@codeGeneratorLLM text
Use codeGeneratorLLM when the task requires syntax-sensitive code generation, code transformation, or structured patches that must preserve programming-language constraints.
Prefer it over writerLLM when exact syntax matters and over js-eval when code still needs to be produced rather than executed inside the runtime.
Good inputs state the target language, environment, preserved context, forbidden changes, desired output shape, and whether the result should be a snippet, full file, or patch-like artifact.
Avoid using it as a general planner, a vague reasoning surface, or a generic prose model.
